{"title":"Equilibrium: investors add AUM X until net alpha = 0 -> alpha_dollars = fee * X","markdown":{"headingText":"Equilibrium: investors add AUM X until net alpha = 0 -> alpha_dollars = fee * X","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"::: {.question}\n\n**Skill, Fees, and Equilibrium AUM **\n\n```{r}\n#| eval: true\n#| echo: false\n#| results: asis\nlibrary(webexercises)\n\nset.seed(505)\ncap_skill   <- round(runif(1, 300, 800), 0)      # capacity with skill (in $ millions)\nalpha_skill <- round(runif(1, 0.012, 0.03), 3)   # skill alpha up to capacity (decimal)\nfee         <- round(runif(1, 0.005, 0.012), 3)  # fee on all AUM (decimal)\n\nalpha_dollars <- cap_skill * 1e6 * alpha_skill   # annual $ alpha at capacity\nAUM_eq        <- alpha_dollars / fee\nfees_dollars  <- AUM_eq * fee\n\nalpha_skill_pct <- round(100*alpha_skill, 2)\nfee_pct         <- round(100*fee, 2)\nAUM_eq_m        <- round(AUM_eq/1e6, 0)\nfees_m          <- round(fees_dollars/1e6, 2)\n```\n\nA manager can generate **α = `r alpha_skill_pct`%** per year up to **$`r cap_skill`m** of capital; above that, incremental α ≈ 0.  \nThe fund charges **`r fee_pct`%** on total AUM. Assume investors flock in until **net α = 0**.\n\n::: {.question-block}\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;\">\n  <label for=\"module5_num_q3a\"><strong>3a. Equilibrium AUM (in $ millions):</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module5_num_q3a\" name=\"module5_num_q3a\" style=\"width:220px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=`r AUM_eq_m` data-tolerance=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module5_num_q3a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n✅ <strong>Equilibrium AUM</strong><br>\nDollar alpha at capacity: α × capacity = `r alpha_skill_pct`% × $`r cap_skill`m = \n<strong>$`r round(alpha_dollars/1e6,2)`m</strong> per year.<br>\nAt equilibrium, investors add capital until **dollar α = fees**:<br>\nfee × AUM = `r fee_pct`% × AUM = $`r round(alpha_dollars/1e6,2)`m ⇒ \nAUM = $`r AUM_eq_m`m (rounded).\n</div>\n:::\n\n::: {.question-block}\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;\">\n  <label for=\"module5_num_q3b\"><strong>3b. Annual fee revenue at equilibrium (in $ millions):</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module5_num_q3b\" name=\"module5_num_q3b\" style=\"width:240px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=`r fees_m` data-tolerance=\"0.1\" step=\"0.01\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module5_num_q3b\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n✅ <strong>Fee revenue at equilibrium</strong><br>\nFee revenue = fee × AUM = `r fee_pct`% × $`r AUM_eq_m`m = \n<strong>$`r fees_m`m</strong> per year.<br>\nNotice this equals the manager’s **dollar α at capacity**: $`r round(alpha_dollars/1e6,2)`m.  \nIntuition: competition drives **net α to investors ≈ 0**; skilled managers capture the rents via fees.\n</div>\n:::\n\n\n:::\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"knitr"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"la